---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AffiliateDisclosureBlock from '../../components/AffiliateDisclosure.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure | TSA Monster"
  description="TSA Monster is an Amazon Associates participant. Learn how our affiliate relationships work, how commissions are earned, and why they never influence our editorial recommendations."
>
  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h1 class="font-display">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>

      <AffiliateDisclosureBlock />

      <p class="lead">
        Transparency is the foundation of useful reviews. This page explains exactly how affiliate
        links work on TSA Monster, what it means for you, and how we ensure our editorial opinions
        remain independent.
      </p>

      <h2>What Is the Amazon Associates Program?</h2>
      <p>
        The Amazon Services LLC Associates Program is an affiliate advertising program that allows
        publishers to earn commissions by linking to products on Amazon.com. TSA Monster is a
        participant in this program.
      </p>
      <p>
        When you click an affiliate link on this site and subsequently make a qualifying purchase on
        Amazon, Amazon pays us a small percentage of the sale price as a commission. The cost to
        you is identical to what you'd pay if you navigated to Amazon directly — we receive a portion
        of what Amazon would otherwise keep.
      </p>

      <h2>How Commissions Work</h2>
      <p>
        Amazon affiliate commissions range from approximately 1% to 10% of the sale price, depending
        on the product category. These commissions help fund the editorial work of researching,
        testing, and writing reviews — maintaining this site as a reader-supported resource rather
        than one dependent on display advertising.
      </p>
      <p>
        Commissions are tied to purchases made within a session after clicking our link — not to
        your purchase history or personal identity. Amazon tracks this via a cookie placed on your
        browser at the time of the click.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate commissions do not determine what we review, how we rate products, or what
        recommendations we make. The products we feature are selected based on what we believe is
        genuinely useful for our readers — not on commission rates.
      </p>
      <p>
        Commission rates vary by category (and are generally low for the types of products we cover).
        A product we believe is mediocre will not receive a positive review because it carries a
        higher commission. A product we think is excellent will receive that recommendation whether
        or not an affiliate link is available.
      </p>
      <p>
        When we recommend a product that has an affiliate link, we disclose that relationship — in
        our <a href="/en/about/">About</a> page, in the footer of every page, and prominently on
        this disclosure page. We believe you deserve to know who benefits from your purchasing
        decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>What This Means for You</h2>
      <p>
        Using our affiliate links is entirely optional. If you prefer, you can search for any
        product we review directly on Amazon or another retailer. Our reviews contain enough
        specifics (model names, product details) to find what you're looking for without using our
        links.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you do use our links, you're supporting independent product research at no extra cost to
        you. We appreciate it — it's what keeps this site going.
      </p>

      <h2>FTC Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        This disclosure is made in accordance with the Federal Trade Commission's guidelines on
        endorsements and testimonials (16 CFR Part 255). The FTC requires that any material
        connection between an endorser and a brand — including financial compensation — be clearly
        disclosed to consumers. Our affiliate relationships constitute such a connection, and we
        disclose them accordingly.
      </p>
      <p>
        Questions about our affiliate practices? Contact us at{' '}
        <a href="mailto:hello@tsa.monster">hello@tsa.monster</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
